body: Same. I'm experiencing it using `2.109.1`, but also when I upgrade to `2.110.0`.
Interestingly a setup that worked yesterday has stopped working with this error. I wonder if the API fastlane is using has started responding differently

@KorvinSzanto That's a strong assumption. None of the related `spaceship` code has changed recently, near as I can tell. Plus, as I noted earlier, this isn't just happening with the latest fastlane version but in prior versions as well. I would not be surprised if this issue is upstream somewhere.

From fastlane's sourcecode (https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/master/spaceship/lib/spaceship/portal/provisioning_profile.rb#L197) maybe I'm missing something, but `adhoc` isn't mentioned in that switch statement. 

I tried using `inhouse` and the result was this:

`Unsupported environment inhouse, must be in appstore, adhoc, development, enterprise`

¯\_(ツ)_/¯

I created a build and everything worked correctly, then tried to create another build 15 minutes later and received the `Can't find class 'adhoc'` error.  Nothing was changed in my fastlane configuration or installation.  My fastlane version is 2.107.0.

Facing the same issue. Things were working fine yesterday
On our end this was working up until about 4.5 hours ago. So `match` was working as expected even earlier today.
@colesteaks I think you're right. I added `case 'adhoc' AdHoc` to that switch statement and it got all the way through

The real question is why `adhoc` is all of a sudden a problem. That switch statement hasn't had a case for `adhoc` anytime recently and it wasn't a problem before.

This does appear limited to `match` actions  that specify the `adhoc` profile thankfully: our testflight builds using the `appstore` profile are unaffected.
It happened to me while using sigh()

distribution method, yet the case statement
wasn't previously handling it.
